<section xml:id="sec-measuring-variability">
  <title>Measuring Variability</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This section covers the various statistical measures used to quantify variability in data.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Learn common measures of variability</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Understand when to use different measures</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Interpret variability measures correctly</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-common-measures">
    <title>Common Measures of Variability</title>
    <p>
      Key measures include range, interquartile range (IQR), variance, standard deviation, and coefficient of variation. Each has its strengths and appropriate uses.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-choosing-measures">
    <title>Choosing Appropriate Measures</title>
    <p>
      The choice of measure depends on the data type, distribution shape, and the presence of outliers. Understanding these factors helps in selecting the right measure.
    </p>
  </subsection>

</section>
